cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "tetrad-lens: a McLuhan-tetrad-shaped attribute schema and three-tier tagger for AI agent traces"
abstract: >
  tetrad-lens is a Langfuse / OpenTelemetry plugin that records the four
  McLuhan tetrad laws (Enhance / Obsolesce / Retrieve / Reverse, from
  McLuhan & McLuhan, Laws of Media: The New Science, University of Toronto
  Press, 1988) as span attributes and ships a three-tier (heuristic +
  LLM-assisted + human-review-queue) tagger. The Engelbart H-LAM/T
  augmentation level is recorded on a secondary axis.
authors:
  - family-names: "tetrad-lens contributors"
type: software
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-05-17
repository-code: "https://github.com/hinanohart/tetrad-lens"
keywords:
  - McLuhan
  - tetrad
  - observability
  - OpenTelemetry
  - Langfuse
  - LLM
  - agent
  - augmentation
